-Uninstall any version of openJDK

-Install Oracle JDK & JRE and set paths for vars

-Install all dependencies (version matters) https://github.com/apache/incubator-metron/tree/master/metron-deployment/vagrant/quick-dev-platform

-For ansible install using: http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/intro_installation.html

-Then downgrade Ansible: https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/METRON/Downgrade+Ansible

-For Maven need to set oracle java path and add maven path http://maven.apache.org/install.html

-Clone incubator-metron https://github.com/apache/incubator-metron in same dir as dependencies

-Follow instructions on git to deploy QUICK-DEV-PLATFORM <or> codelab-platform

*If receiving "error occurred while installing ffi (1.9.14)" during vagrant host-manager install" then:
1) curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --ruby
2) gem install compass
3) gem install ffi -v '1.9.14'

Install Packet-Capture Tools
-install wireshark using your software/package manager
-install python-dev & python3-dev & libpython-dev & libpython3-dev & libpacp0.8 & libpcap-dev & libpcap0.8dev using package manager
-install python-pcapy and python-libpcap using your package manager
-install pcapy using instructions here: https://github.com/CoreSecurity/pcapy
-install kafka-python using instructions here: https://github.com/dpkp/kafka-python
-cd incubator-metron/metron-sensors/pycapa, install pycapa using instrcutions here: https://github.com/apache/incubator-metron/tree/master/metron-sensors/pycapa
